{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed framework for the autonomous refinement of Agentic AI systems has certain limitations that warrant consideration.",
    "Using LLMs for feedback, hypothesis formation, and evaluation may lead to inaccuracies, lack of explainability, and biases stemming from their training data.",
    "The framework's effectiveness relies on well-defined evaluation criteria.",
    "Poor or biased criteria can result in suboptimal refinements, as agents cannot independently identify missing dimensions.",
    "Minimal human involvement can be problematic in highstakes or ambiguous tasks, where nuanced judgment and ethical considerations, such as privacy or unintended consequences, are crucial."
  ]
}